    "recap_headline": "Northwestern University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "EUGENE, Ore. \u2013\nNorthwestern was unable to complete the comeback at No. 21 Oregon in a 6-4 setback on Saturday afternoon at PK Park.\nC\nJay Slater\nhad a standout day both at the plate and behind the plate. Slater slugged his third homer of the season and caught a runner stealing at second base in the contest.\nLHP\nJake Rifenburg\nwas solid in relief, allowing one run on four hits and zero walks, striking out three in 5.1 innings pitched.\nOregon (19-3, 7-1 Big Ten) got on the scoreboard first, drawing first blood on a two-run homer by INF Drew Smith in the bottom of the first.\nNorthwestern (7-11-1, 1-4 Big Ten) evened the score at two apiece with a pair of runs in the top of the second. With INF\nNick Barron\non first base, INF\nOwen McElfatrick\ndoubled him to third to put a couple of runners in scoring position. OF\nJack Lausch\ndrove in Barron with a sacrifice fly for the first run, and INF\nNoah Ruiz\nplated McElfatrick on a fielder's choice to even the game at two.\nThe Ducks responded to plate three in the second and added another in the fourth to stretch their lead to four.\nSlater brought the Wildcats back within two with a two-run blast to left-center, scoring Ruiz.\nRHP Collin Clarke (4-1) surrendered four earned runs on five hits and two walks, striking out 10 for the Ducks.\nRHP\nGarrett Shearer\n(0-1) is credited with the loss, allowing five runs on five hits and two walks, fanning one in 2.2 innings pitched.\nSunday's series finale is scheduled for 2:05 p.m. CT on B1G+. RHP\nMatt Kouser\nis set to make the start for the Wildcats, with RHP Cal Scolari slated to start for Oregon.",
